Google has launched Hire, a recruiting app that integrates with its G Suite platform, which includes apps like Gmail and Google Calendar. News of the service emerged earlier this year when the Google Hire website launched with a public sign-in page. Several tech companies appeared to be testing the service, including Medisas, Poynt, DramaFever, SingleHop, and CoreOS. Hire includes the following features: All US-based businesses under 1,000 employees that use G Suite can now purchase Hire. Google is also accepting demo requests for the service.